# Normalize all text files to LF in the working tree on every platform.
# The engine writes its generated/committed files with '\n' (e.g. the
# blueprint gallery in engine/lib/bpcheck.js), and the proof suite compares
# those files byte-for-byte against a fresh regeneration (proof 11). Without
# this, a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true stores them as CRLF and
# proof 11 reports a phantom "stale gallery" on every clean clone.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize or diff as text.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.webp binary
*.avif binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
